## 2. Change 1 & 2: `shared` Module Architecture

The `common` module has been renamed to `shared` to align with DDD and enterprise standards. This module encapsulates cross-cutting concerns used by all current and future modules.

### 2.1 Package Structure and Responsibilities

```text
com.farmerai.companion.shared
├── config          → Global application configuration (e.g., Jackson, async executors).
├── exception       → Global `@ControllerAdvice` and standard error mappings.
├── logging         → MDC tracing, `LoggingInterceptor`, `CorrelationIdFilter`.
├── response        → Standardized API wrappers (`ApiResponse<T>`, `PagedResponse<T>`).
├── validation      → Custom Bean Validation constraints and validators.
└── audit           → JPA auditing, `BaseEntity`, `AuditorAware`.
```

| Package | Responsibility | Future Microservices Impact |
|---------|----------------|-----------------------------|
| `config` | Centralized Spring configuration. | Will be extracted into a shared library (e.g., `companion-starter-web`). |
| `exception` | Consistent error handling across APIs. | Ensures all microservices return the exact same error format. |
| `logging` | Distributed tracing preparation. | Correlation IDs will pass seamlessly across service boundaries. |
| `response` | Unified API envelope structure. | Standardizes contracts across all frontend-backend interactions. |
| `validation` | Reusable validation logic. | Shared validation rules across bounded contexts. |
| `audit` | Entity tracking and optimistic locking. | Ensures consistent data governance across decentralized databases. |

