## 3. Change 3: Production-Grade `shared.response`

To guarantee frontend predictability, **all** APIs will return a consistent JSON envelope.

### 3.1 Generic Design

```json
{
   "success": true,
   "message": "Operation Successful",
   "data": { ... payload ... },
   "timestamp": "2026-06-20T12:00:00"
}
```

### 3.2 Class Diagram

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class ApiResponse~T~ {
        +boolean success
        +String message
        +T data
        +Instant timestamp
        +success(T data, String message)$ ApiResponse~T~
        +error(String message)$ ApiResponse~Void~
    }

    class PagedResponse~T~ {
        +int page
        +int size
        +long totalElements
        +int totalPages
        +boolean hasNext
        +of(Page~T~ page)$ PagedResponse~T~
    }

    ApiResponse *-- PagedResponse : data
```

### 3.3 Responsibilities
*   **`ApiResponse<T>`**: The standard envelope. `success` dictates if the business operation succeeded. `message` provides human-readable context. `data` holds the actual payload.
*   **`PagedResponse<T>`**: Standardizes pagination metadata, used inside the `data` field of `ApiResponse` when returning collections.

