## 8. Change 8: Future-Proof RefreshToken Design

To support advanced session management (logout from specific device, view active sessions), we will enrich the `RefreshToken` entity.

### 8.1 Updated Entity

```text
RefreshToken
├── id: UUID
├── token: TokenValue
├── userId: UUID
├── deviceId: String         (New: Unique hardware/browser ID)
├── deviceName: String       (New: e.g., "Samsung S24")
├── platform: String         (New: e.g., "Android")
├── lastUsedAt: Instant      (New: Updated on every refresh)
├── expiryDate: Instant
└── isRevoked: boolean
```

### 8.2 Database Schema Impact

```sql
ALTER TABLE refresh_tokens 
ADD COLUMN device_id VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
ADD COLUMN device_name VARCHAR(255),
ADD COLUMN platform VARCHAR(50),
ADD COLUMN last_used_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW();

CREATE INDEX idx_refresh_tokens_user_device ON refresh_tokens(user_id, device_id);
```

### 8.3 ER Diagram Changes

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS ||--o{ REFRESH_TOKENS : "has multiple active sessions"

    REFRESH_TOKENS {
        uuid id PK
        varchar(512) token UK
        uuid user_id FK
        varchar(255) device_id "NOT NULL (e.g., UUID from mobile)"
        varchar(255) device_name "(e.g., iPhone 15)"
        varchar(50) platform "(iOS, Android, Web)"
        timestamp last_used_at "NOT NULL"
        timestamp expiry_date "NOT NULL"
        boolean is_revoked "NOT NULL"
    }
```

### 8.4 Sequence Diagram Impact (Login Flow)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant AuthAppService
    participant RefreshTokenRepo

    Client->>AuthAppService: login(email, password, deviceId, deviceName, platform)
    AuthAppService->>AuthAppService: Validate Credentials
    
    AuthAppService->>RefreshTokenRepo: findByUserIdAndDeviceId()
    alt Existing Device Session Found
        AuthAppService->>RefreshTokenRepo: revoke(oldToken)
    end
    
    AuthAppService->>RefreshTokenRepo: save(newRefreshToken with device metadata)
    AuthAppService-->>Client: AuthResult (Access + Refresh Tokens)
```

**Impact:**
1.  **Logout current device:** Simply revoke the token matching the `deviceId` in the request.
2.  **Logout all devices:** Call `revokeAllByUserId(userId)`.
3.  **Active sessions UI:** Frontend can query `/api/v1/auth/sessions` to list active devices (using `deviceName`, `platform`, `lastUsedAt`).

